EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

Sutter Home Winery, Inc. has established a risk management plan according to EPA's regulations (40 CFR Part 68) for the Ammonia Refrigeration System at its Main Street Facility to enhance its already existing safety programs.  Sutter Home is extremely cautious in the handling of all chemicals and is very diligent about safety for its employees and its communities.  Sutter Home staff is highly trained and utilizes modern equipment to provide safeguards.  The Ammonia Refrigeration System, that contains the regulated substance anhydrous ammonia, is used for chilling wine and for cooling down wine storage tanks and maintaining them at a cold temperature.  


Accidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response Policies

Sutter Home has an emergency response plan in effect to handle potential emergency situations at this facility.  This plan was designed to meet the following objectives:

1.) To save lives.
2.) To minimize and avoid injuries.
3.) To protect the environment.
4.) To minimize property damage.

Key elements of the Emergency Response Plan include key phone numbers and contact points, plans for evacuation, fire, injury, earthquake, hazardous material spill, and ammonia health hazards 


Stationary Source and Regulated Substance

The ammonia refrigeration system at the Sutter Home Main Street plant is made up of two refrigeration plants.

Refrigeration Plant #1 contains the following components:

7 Two (2) 350 hp, Mycom 200VMD screw compressors;
7 Four (4) 125 hp, Mycom N6B reciprocating compressors;
7 One (1) 75 hp, Mycom N8WA reciprocating compressors;
7 One (1) 75 hp, Mycom N8A reciprocating compressor
7 One (1) BAC VC2-642 Evaporative condenser;
7 Two  (2) BAC C2-443 KD Evaporative condensers;
7 One  (1) BAC VXMC-340 Evaporative condenser;
7 One  (1) BAC VLC-350 Evaporative condenser;
7 Two (2) Horizontal cylindrical High Pressure Receivers;
7 Two (2) Vertical low pressure Suction Traps;
7 Three (3) Ammonia pumps 
7 Four (4) Wine chillers

;
7 Three (3) Glycol chillers (In conjunction with Refrigeration Plant #2);
7 One (1) Ice maker(In conjunction with Refrigeration Plant #2);
7 Four (4) Air handlers;
7 Several relief valves, gas regulating valves, gate valves, solenoid valves, check valves, level switches, expansion valves; and
7 Piping and other ancillary equipment.

